Welcome to `Web Dev Flow`, a “roadmap” designed to teach newcomers the fundamentals of web development. 

Whether you are looking to start a career in web development or simply want to learn how to create your own web apps, this course will provide you with the knowledge and skills you need to get started. 

This “roadmap” will cover the basics of web development, both Frontend and Backend, as well as popular frameworks and tools. Join us on this exciting journey into the world of web development and start creating your own web projects today!

In order to get started, just follow the arrows. Each arrow represent a dependency, but of course you can always skip and go directly to more advanced topics.

Practicing the material is an essential aspect of learning and mastering any new skill, and web development is no exception. When you practice what you have learned, you reinforce your understanding of the concepts, and you gain the confidence to apply them in real-world situations

It is recommended to do the exercises along the way.

`Web Dev Flow` is based on `Excaliflow`, a web application aimed to enable mentors to easily create beautiful flows based on [Excalidraw](https://excalidraw.com/) and to enable mentees to mark their progress along the way. 

`Excaliflow` is maintained in Github [yeger00/excalidraw-app](https://github.com/yeger00/excalidraw-app).
